@startuml sequence_request_logging
!theme plain

title Request Logging Pipeline

actor Client
participant "CorrelationId\nMiddleware" as CorrMw
participant "Logging\nMiddleware" as LogMw
participant "Metrics\nCollector" as Metrics
participant "Route\nHandler" as Handler
participant "Log\nAggregator" as Logs

Client -> CorrMw: HTTP Request
note right of CorrMw
  Check X-Correlation-ID header.
  If absent, generate UUIDv4.
end note
CorrMw -> CorrMw: Attach correlation_id\nto request context

CorrMw -> LogMw: Forward request
LogMw -> LogMw: Record start time,\nextract method, path, user_id
LogMw -> Metrics: Increment http_requests_total

LogMw -> Handler: Forward request
Handler --> LogMw: Response (status_code)

LogMw -> LogMw: Compute duration_ms
LogMw -> Metrics: Observe http_request_duration_seconds
LogMw -> Logs: Emit structured JSON log entry
note right of Logs
  { timestamp, severity, correlation_id,
    method, path, status_code,
    duration_ms, user_id }
end note

LogMw --> Client: Response with\nX-Correlation-ID header

@enduml
